movies.title: The Power of the Dog
movies.resume: Charismatic rancher Phil Burbank inspires fear and awe in those around him. When his brother brings home a new wife and her son, Phil torments them until he finds himself exposed to the possibility of love.

movies.title: Drive my car
movies.resume: Nishijima Hidetoshi is a stage actor and director happily married to his playwright wife. Then one day she disappears.

movies.title: Licorice Pizza
movies.resume: The story of Alana Kane and Gary Valentine growing up, running around and going through the treacherous navigation of first love in the San Fernando Valley, 1973.

movies.title: The Worst Person in the World
movies.resume: The chronicles of four years in the life of Julie, a young woman who navigates the troubled waters of her love life and struggles to find her career path, leading her to take a realistic look at who she really is.

movies.title: Portrait of a Lady on Fire.
movies.resume: On an isolated island in Brittany at the end of the eighteenth century, a female painter is obliged to paint a wedding portrait of a young woman.

movies.title: Nomadland
movies.resume: A woman in her sixties, after losing everything in the Great Recession, embarks on a journey through the American West, living as a van-dwelling modern-day nomad.

movies.title: Never Rarely Sometimes Always
movies.resume: A pair of teenage girls in rural Pennsylvania travel to New York City to seek out medical help after an unintended pregnancy.

movies.title: First Cow
movies.resume: A skilled cook has traveled west and joined a group of fur trappers in Oregon, though he only finds true connection with a Chinese immigrant also seeking his fortune. Soon the two collaborate on a successful business.

movies.title: Parasite
movies.resume: Greed and class discrimination threaten the newly formed symbiotic relationship between the wealthy Park family and the destitute Kim clan.

movies.title: The Irishman
movies.resume: Hitman Frank Sheeran looks back at the secrets he kept as a loyal member of the Bufalino crime family.

movies.title: The Shawshank Redemption
movies.resume: Two imprisoned men bond over a number of years, finding solace and eventual redemption through acts of common decency.

movies.title: The Godfather
movies.resume: The Godfather follows Vito Corleone, Don of the Corleone family, as he passes the mantel to his unwilling son, Michael.

movies.title: The Dark Knight
movies.resume: When the menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham, Batman must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice.

movies.title: 12 Angry Men
movies.resume: The jury in a New York City murder trial is frustrated by a single member whose skeptical caution forces them to more carefully consider the evidence before jumping to a hasty verdict.

movies.title: Schindler's List
movies.resume: In German-occupied Poland during World War II, industrialist Oskar Schindler gradually becomes concerned for his Jewish workforce after witnessing their persecution by the Nazis.

movies.title: The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring
movies.resume: A meek Hobbit from the Shire and eight companions set out on a journey to destroy the powerful One Ring and save Middle-earth from the Dark Lord Sauron.

movies.title: Spider-Man: No Way Home
movies.resume: With Spider-Man's identity now revealed, Peter asks Doctor Strange for help. When a spell goes wrong, dangerous foes from other worlds start to appear, forcing Peter to discover what it truly means to be Spider-Man.

movies.title: Pulp Fiction
movies.resume: The lives of two mob hitmen, a boxer, a gangster and his wife, and a pair of diner bandits intertwine in four tales of violence and redemption.

movies.title: Fight Club
movies.resume: An insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soap maker form an underground fight club that evolves into much more.

movies.title: Inception
movies.resume: A thief who steals corporate secrets through the use of dream-sharing technology is given the inverse task of planting an idea into the mind of a C.E.O., but his tragic past may doom the project and his team to disaster.

movies.title: The Matrix
movies.resume: When a beautiful stranger leads computer hacker Neo to a forbidding underworld, he discovers the shocking truth--the life he knows is the elaborate deception of an evil cyber-intelligence.

movies.title: Kill Bill Volume 1
movies.resume: After awakening from a four-year coma, a former assassin wreaks vengeance on the team of assassins who betrayed her.

movies.title: Don't Look Up
movies.resume: Two low-level astronomers must go on a giant media tour to warn mankind of an approaching comet that will destroy planet Earth.

movies.title: Home Alone
movies.resume: An eight-year-old troublemaker must protect his house from a pair of burglars when he is accidentally left home alone by his family during Christmas vacation.

movies.title: Love Actually
movies.resume: Follows the lives of eight very different couples in dealing with their love lives in various loosely interrelated tales all set during a frantic month before Christmas in London, UK.
